GRAPH <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Digest_PackagingEntitlement> {
  <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Digest_PackagingEntitlement> a narr:Digest ;
    narr:digestOf <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#PackagingEntitlement> ;
    narr:childCount "30"^^xsd:integer ;
    narr:generatedFrom "d1b09a828565de86" ;
    narr:narration """This hub packages aswritten's capability tiers and how plans gate them. The mainline runs Free → Expert → Team → Org. [Free is read-only](narr:Claim_FreeTierReadOnly_DesignSession) — load perspectives, no saving — which is the deliberate gate driving the upgrade. [Expert is single-stream](narr:Claim_ExpertSingleStreamNoGitBranching): memories commit to main with [synchronous self-review](narr:Claim_ExpertTierSyncReview), no branches/PRs by default, and it functions as [a feeder / near paid-demo](narr:Claim_ExpertTierAsPaidDemo) rather than a standalone business. [Team adds multi-user contribution](narr:Claim_TeamTierGitHubBranch) to one worldview, where the [sales call is itself onboarding + first extraction](narr:Narrative_SalesCallIsOnboarding). [Org bundles three capabilities](narr:Claim_OrgTierThreeCapabilities) — sandboxed internal AI, external agent deployments, and EDOs — reached by [any of three triggers](narr:Claim_OrgTierThreeUpgradeTriggers) (100+ seats, agent deployment, or EDO). Mechanically, gating is [compile returning plan-level instruction sets](narr:Claim_PlanGatedInstructionsFromCompile), not separate tools. The [admin tier was eliminated](narr:Claim_AdminTierEliminated) (Mar 2026). A recurring reframe (Jul 2025, Apr 2026) holds that [GitHub × team size are the real axes](narr:Narrative_TierAxisGitHubTeamSize) and tiers are packaging on top.""" ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_AdminTierEliminated> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_CompileReturnsPlanGatedInstructions> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_ExpertSingleStreamNoGitBranching> ;
